    <h1>Ito Calculus</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">MIT OCW 18.S096 + 15.450 (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Ito calculus</strong> extends the chain rule to functions of Brownian motion. The extra term &#x2014; the &#xBD;&#x03C3;&#xB2;f&#x2033; correction &#x2014; exists because Brownian motion has nonzero quadratic variation. This is the engine behind every option pricing formula.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Ito's lemma diagram -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 180" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
